oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Eagleville high school graduating class, 1935
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This photograph is a "Back When Luttrell History Item," which was prepared on April 27, 2000 by Woodrow Luttrell, husband of Gladys Carlton, a member of the class.

First row, seated (L to R): Earl Taylor, Billy Landis, William Pettus, Gene Taylor,Jasper Scott, Grover Ed Maxwell, G. C. Marable, Will T. Vaughan, and Robert Ralston. Second row, standing (L to R): Roy Dowdy, Principal, (Married names are included) Gladys CarltoIi, Lola Pearl Hall, Mary T. Taylor, Mary Catherine Neal, Louise Zumbro, Edna Kelly, Geneva Stanford, and Sara Redmon. Note: These names agree with those identified with the City of Eagleville photo used in the story by Dan Whittle in his "Roamin' Middle Tennessee" column thatappeared in The Daily News Journal (Murfreesboro, TN) on Sunday, March 14, 2004. That date was after the passing of Gladys Carlton Luttrell on February, 17,2004.
